  "body": "### Description\r\nAs a validator, I want to submit a potentially invalid signed Validator Exit Message(VEM) so that I can exit.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\nA characterized error mentioning why the VEM is invalid.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n`curl -X POST \"http://127.0.0.1:5051/eth/v1/beacon/pool/voluntary_exits\"  -H \"accept: application/json\" -d '{\"message\":{\"epoch\":\"0\",\"validator_index\":\"111075\"},\"signature\":\"0x90321cc3fef91133b96fcbd5620907219dd15db5a33c306cce1a30d5c53dbeb2171e0f6e00bd66ef6cfb550a71fb84d006461398c729d17e45d648180ae75b388efc1a0b36eedb63c433339ddc0851dbf0c49386a00a5a60f46f822a8ae28114\"}'`\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\n{\"status\":400,\"message\":\"Invalid voluntary exit, the exit epoch is too early\"} (this is an example)\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:**\r\n{\"status\":400,\"message\":\"Invalid voluntary exit, it will never pass validation so it's rejected\"}\r\n\r\nFor all possible error see VEM processing:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/phase0/beacon-chain.md#voluntary-exits",
