    "body": "Note for the future implementer/fixer, the problem shows up not only on the API but using the CLI commands as well, for example \r\n`./build/install/teku/bin/teku --network=pyrmont voluntary-exit --validators-external-signer-public-keys=0x964ad3bc2f60dc0523cc5e6626083f0678ac2623896222e6b81f1ce2108486c76be280daa44958e96a4f090ee03b1d62 --validators-external-signer-url=http://127.0.0.1:9100/` result in a valid VEM but invalid because epoch is too early resulting with the same ¬´ Invalid voluntary exit, it will never pass validation so it's rejected ¬ª so maybe there is also something on the default epoch selection for the CLI.",
